Now consider Equations~(\ref{Q3:m}) and~(\ref{Q3:n}).  These show that _____ and _____ so that <m>m</m> and <m>n</m> share a common factor of _____, and thus <m>\frac{m}{n}</m> is not in lowest terms.  This is _____.  Moreover, this contradiction proves that our assumption that <m>\sqrt{3}</m> is rational _____, and therefore <m>\sqrt{3}</m> is irrational.
