  </subsection>
  <subsection>
    <title>More Proofs by Contradiction</title>
    <activity workspace="1in">
      <statement>
        <p>Try to determine if the following conjectures are true on false. If true, work on the proving the following theorems by contradiction.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>For each real number <m>x</m>, if <m>0&lt;x&lt;1</m> then <m>\frac{1}{x(1-x)}\ge 4</m>.</p></li>
          <li><p>Let <m>a, b,</m> and <m>c</m> be integers. If <m>3\mid a</m> and <m>3\mid b</m> and <m>c\equiv 1 \pmod{3}</m> then the equation <m>ax+by=c</m> has no solution in which both <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are integers.</p></li>
          <li><p>For each positive real number <m>x</m>, if <m>x</m> is irrational then <m>x^2</m> is irrational.</p></li>
        </ul>
      </statement>
    </activity>
  </subsection>
</worksheet>
